diff --git a/malloc/jemalloc/README.md b/malloc/jemalloc/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..9a7e6a75a7
--- /dev/null
+++ b/malloc/jemalloc/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+In-tree copy of jemalloc for embedding into glibc.
+
+Sources under `src/` and headers under `include/` are vendored together
+with configure-generated headers produced by:
+
+  ./configure --with-jemalloc-prefix=je_ --disable-shared --enable-static \
+              --disable-cxx --with-lg-page=12 --disable-initial-exec-tls \
+              --without-export --disable-libdl --disable-stats
+
+`LG_SIZEOF_PTR` is made portable via `__SIZEOF_POINTER__`.  `LG_PAGE` is
+fixed at 12 (4 KiB), matching the common Linux default.  The Darwin
+`zone.c` allocator and C++ wrapper are omitted.  `JEMALLOC_HAVE_PROCESS_MADVISE`
+is disabled because glibc's internal syscall headers do not expose
+`SYS_process_madvise` consistently at compile time.
+
+Compiled as individual translation units listed in `malloc/Makefile`
+(`jemalloc-routines`).  Update by re-running configure with the flags
+above and replacing `src/` + `include/`.
